rc=http--braggarts.shareplay.com-pics-Wythe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Maujer Niteblind</span><hr size=1> Maujer paced around the hall, glaring aimlessly at the bag seller, the begger, the Keep guards standing endlessly at attention.<br>
<br>
Her slippered foot tapped impatiently again as she waited for her aunt to show up--late as usual, as always--you'd think a bard running fast as light could be on time. But no--Aunt Vainne was late again. She had probably stopped to watch the novices begin their crafts in the commonlands, or was trying to seek revenge (again) against the dead in Kithikor (a futile pastime).<br>
<br>
Sighing, the young Erudite moved her arms and recast a few simple spells. Practice, practice, as her guildmasters advised. One does not run before walking, walk before crawling--<br>
<br>
&quot;--and I do little of anything,&quot; Maujer thought bitterly to herself not for the first time. Her green eyes sparkled with anger, her lip curled in a slight pout. She was bored of her practice, bored of her craft before it had even begun. In her short life what had she done? Not very much, not nearly enough. Her fingers itched to go outside the safe walls of Highhold, to help the apprentice troops guarding the passes from gnolls on one side and orcs on the other...to do...something....<br>
<br>
A traveller, bronze armour creased with dust, face sweatstained, shield on hand hurried past. Maujer wasn't sure if there was an air of the caster around him or not but just to be sure, just to do--something--she raised her arms and whispered the incantation.<br>
<br>
The traveller sighed in tranquility and went on his way into the halls of the Keep. <p><b>Vainne K'harmicdeva
